pull_request.title: Support web proxy in external interop tests
pull_request.body:
Update oqsprovider-externalinterop.sh to support web proxy in external interop tests. To determine whether to resort to proxy handling, checks if env var `HTTP_PROXY` is set

Fixes #282

pull_request.title: chore(ci): Run CI checks on merge groups
Pull new HQC implementation from upstream
pull_request.body:
<!-- Please give a brief explanation of the purpose of this pull request. -->
Run copy_from_upstream to pull the [recently merged](https://github.com/PQClean/PQClean/pull/512) HQC updates from PQClean. Ignore Kyber and Dilithium updates as we don't yet want to move to the "standard" version.

<!-- Does this PR resolve any issue?  If so, please reference it using automatic-closing keywords like "Fixes #123." -->
Fixes #1319.

* [x] Does this PR change the input/output behaviour of a cryptographic algorithm (i.e., does it change known answer test values)?  (If so, a version bump will be required from *x.y.z* to *x.(y+1).0*.)
* [ ] Does this PR change the list of algorithms available -- either adding, removing, or renaming? Does this PR otherwise change an API? (If so, PRs in fully supported downstream projects dependent on these, i.e., [oqs-provider](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/oqs-provider) and [OQS-OpenSSH](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssh) will also need to be ready for review and merge by the time this is merged.)

pull_request.title: Updates docker file to create test server package
pull_request.body:
The update uses..
- liboqs 0.9.0
- latest oqs-provider (main)
- latest nginx 1.25.2

Also updates the nginx docker demo to v1.25.2.
Note that with [nginx 1.25.2](http://nginx.org/en/CHANGES), the location of the openssl config file needs to be passed as an env variable. This is reflected in the Dockerfile of the nginx demo.

The updated package is already deployed at test.openquantumsafe.org.
A test run with `testrun.sh` passes.
I'll update the server again to a tagged oqs-provider release once available.
